AboutAbout

Im a Business Intelligence Developer at Northwestern University, where I design and optimize data visualizations, reports, and automation workflows to improve decision-making across departments. Over the past 2.5 years, Ive worked extensively with IBM Cognos Analytics, Tableau, SQL, and Power Automate, helping teams streamline reporting and access insights more efficiently.

My role involves building and optimizing dashboards, writing complex SQL queries, and integrating BI tools with cloud and automation solutions. Ive also worked closely with ETL teams to improve data pipelines and reporting structures. Recently, Ive been exploring cloud-based BI solutions by incorporating AWS S3, Power Automate, and Azure Functions into automation workflows.

To further develop my cloud and data engineering skills, Im currently taking advanced coursework at Northwestern University, focusing on cloud analytics, data automation, and scalable BI solutions. My goal is to transition into Cloud BI & Analytics Engineering, where I can apply my experience in BI, SQL, and automation to cloud-based data environments.

Ive always been passionate about using technology to solve real-world business problems, whether thats optimizing reporting workflows, automating manual processes, or debugging complex data issues.

Languages: SQL, Python, R
BI & Visualization: IBM Cognos Analytics, Tableau, Power BI
Cloud & Data Engineering: AWS (S3, Redshift), Azure Functions, Power Automate
Other Tools: Google Colab, MongoDB, Knime, MS Project, Excel

Github Portfolio: https://github.com/mkimball14/Max_Portfolio

  • Maximilian KimballMaximilian Kimball You You Cloud BI Developer | AWS | SQL | Power BI | Tableau | Automation | AzureCloud BI Developer | AWS | SQL | Power BI | Tableau | Automation | Azure 1w Edited 1 week ago
    ' & !

    I built a crypto sentiment analysis tool that checks if social media posts about crypto are positive or negative, and tries to predict future sentiment over the next few days. Learned a ton about cloud deployment.

    What I made:
    - FastAPI web service with ML sentiment analysis
    - Used AWS SageMaker for model training
    - Set up Redshift for analyzing sentiment data
    - Containerized everything with Docker
    - Hosted it all on EC2 with S3 storage
    - Added GitHub Actions for automatic deployments

    Getting this running in the cloud was challenging. I had to figure out Docker, AWS configuration, and CI/CD pipelines all at once. Even though my forecast model only had data from January 2021, building this end-to-end solution taught me so much about real-world cloud architecture.

    The next step is to connect to live API and price data to get real-time sentiment predictions and make the model more accurate.

    Check out my GitHub repo if you're interested:
    https://lnkd.in/gw2snYce

    Managing security in cloud environments can be a challenge, especially when working with platforms like SharePoint and OneDrive.

    I recently built an automation using Power Automate and Azure Functions to help identify potential security risks in uploaded files.

    How It Works:
     triggers a workflow when a new file is added.
     () processes the file contents.
     - flags potential security risks like API keys or credentials.
     notify teams when action is needed.

    Why This Matters

    Manually reviewing files for sensitive data is time-consuming and inefficient.
    By automating security checks, teams can catch issues early and improve compliance without disrupting workflows.

    Next Steps

    Im currently exploring:
     Integrating AI-powered detection models to improve accuracy.
     Expanding support for AWS Lambda to make it multi-cloud.
     Optimizing automation workflows for large-scale environments.

    Would love to connect with others working in Cloud BI, Security, and DevOps!
